<L>__{interior liepold's quarters night}
<A>__{liepold at his desk, typing again. this time there is no doubt he is composing a letter denouncing schindler.}
<L>__{interior house brinnlitz night}
<A>__{schindler and emilie, her arm in his, stand around like unwanted guests at the party. they probably are. him anyway. the other guests include local politicians who fought and failed to keep his camp out of brinnlitz. whenever his glance meets one of theirs, they smile tightly.}
<C>__{schindler}
<P>__{(to emilie)}
<D>__{isn't this nice.}
<A>__{it's not at all nice. he feels out of place, a feeling he's not accustomed to. fortunately, a man in uniform, someone schindler can relate to, approaches cheerfully, his hand outstretched.}
